00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:36,266 --> 00:00:39,060
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

2
00:00:42,272 --> 00:00:43,314
<i>When was</i>

3
00:00:44,107 --> 00:00:47,110
<i>the hardest time in your life?</i>

4
00:00:51,155 --> 00:00:51,990
<i>I see</i>

5
00:00:52,991 --> 00:00:55,577
<i>you've never talked about it before.</i>

6
00:00:59,372 --> 00:01:02,375
<i>My friend and I</i>
<i>were taking the subway home after dinner</i>

7
00:01:03,001 --> 00:01:04,210
<i>when they suddenly asked,</i>

8
00:01:05,128 --> 00:01:08,464
<i>"When was the hardest time in your life?"</i>

9
00:01:10,425 --> 00:01:12,427
<i>My heart suddenly started pounding.</i>

10
00:01:14,137 --> 00:01:16,181
<i>I couldn't answer for a long time,</i>

11
00:01:17,473 --> 00:01:19,559
<i>and before I burst into tears,</i>

12
00:01:19,642 --> 00:01:21,019
<i>I just got off.</i>

13
00:01:25,106 --> 00:01:26,357
<i>That day,</i>

14
00:01:26,441 --> 00:01:28,943
<i>I sobbed all the way home.</i>

15
00:01:30,445 --> 00:01:31,738
<i>When I thought about it,</i>

16
00:01:33,323 --> 00:01:35,992
<i>I realized I'd never said out loud</i>
<i>what had happened</i>

17
00:01:37,201 --> 00:01:38,119
<i>back then.</i>

18
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:42,582
<i>The most terrifying part was that,</i>

19
00:01:43,207 --> 00:01:45,543
<i>even at a young age, I was conscious.</i>

20
00:01:46,628 --> 00:01:50,798
<i>I knew being conscious</i>
<i>meant I was experiencing this vivid fear,</i>

21
00:01:51,674 --> 00:01:54,177
<i>but I didn't know how to make it stop.</i>

22
00:01:55,845 --> 00:01:58,723
<i>All I could do was endure that fear</i>
<i>in vivid detail,</i>

23
00:01:58,806 --> 00:02:01,601
<i>completely helpless and overwhelmed by it.</i>

24
00:02:04,354 --> 00:02:05,980
<i>What I wanted the most</i>

25
00:02:07,023 --> 00:02:08,816
<i>was to grow up quickly</i>

26
00:02:09,943 --> 00:02:12,528
<i>so I could leave at any time,</i>
<i>as if it were nothing.</i>

27
00:02:12,612 --> 00:02:13,947
CLOSED UNTIL THE END OF DECEMBER

28
00:02:14,030 --> 00:02:15,823
<i>I thought about how nice it would be</i>

29
00:02:16,741 --> 00:02:18,284
<i>to reach an age</i>
<i>where walking alone at night</i>

30
00:02:18,910 --> 00:02:20,119
<i>was normal.</i>

31
00:02:23,623 --> 00:02:25,124
<i>I was just sitting there…</i>

32
00:02:27,418 --> 00:02:28,920
<i>when my nose started to bleed.</i>

33
00:02:31,297 --> 00:02:33,633
<i>Crows kept gathering outside the window.</i>

34
00:02:35,260 --> 00:02:36,177
<i>I thought,</i>

35
00:02:37,345 --> 00:02:38,763
<i>"I must be dying."</i>

36
00:02:44,143 --> 00:02:44,978
<i>That's…</i>

37
00:02:48,773 --> 00:02:50,316
<i>when my dad came home</i>

38
00:02:52,151 --> 00:02:53,444
after 28 days.

39
00:02:56,114 --> 00:02:57,073
And my mom…

40
00:02:58,908 --> 00:03:00,535
never came back.

41
00:03:03,246 --> 00:03:04,372
I've never once

42
00:03:05,039 --> 00:03:07,000
talked about what happened then.

43
00:03:09,377 --> 00:03:11,713
I think I lived
by consciously blocking it out.

44
00:03:13,214 --> 00:03:14,090
And then

45
00:03:15,675 --> 00:03:18,761
when my friend asked
when the hardest time of my life was,

46
00:03:20,346 --> 00:03:23,057
I felt a surge of rage,
as if it had just happened yesterday.

47
00:03:25,184 --> 00:03:26,144
Before that,

48
00:03:27,311 --> 00:03:29,439
I didn't feel much
whenever I saw my mom's face

49
00:03:30,606 --> 00:03:31,983
pop up in random places,

50
00:03:32,984 --> 00:03:35,111
as if she had nothing to do with me.

51
00:03:36,070 --> 00:03:37,739
But once I felt that rage…

52
00:03:39,991 --> 00:03:42,035
I couldn't stand to look at her face.

53
00:03:44,412 --> 00:03:46,289
<i>The cause of all my pain.</i>

54
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:49,375
What happened then…

55
00:03:51,627 --> 00:03:53,087
and the one behind it.

56
00:03:55,548 --> 00:03:56,382
Mom.

57
00:03:59,677 --> 00:04:01,346
The one who left me behind…

58
00:04:03,973 --> 00:04:05,016
was my mom.

59
00:04:09,562 --> 00:04:12,690
Being over 30 means you've lived
more than ten thousand days.

60
00:04:14,317 --> 00:04:15,985
But whenever anything happens,

61
00:04:17,153 --> 00:04:19,447
I end up going back to those 28 days,

62
00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:22,950
as if they are what made me
who I am today.

63
00:04:24,952 --> 00:04:26,329
I hate talking about wounds.

64
00:04:27,663 --> 00:04:29,791
It feels like the language of the weak.

65
00:04:32,085 --> 00:04:32,919
But…

66
00:04:35,755 --> 00:04:37,256
that's what I'm doing right now.

67
00:04:38,966 --> 00:04:40,510
Whenever something goes wrong,

68
00:04:41,094 --> 00:04:42,929
I tell myself I was shattered back then,

69
00:04:44,263 --> 00:04:46,349
and that's why I'm like this now.

70
00:04:48,309 --> 00:04:50,144
I connect everything back to that time.

71
00:04:52,438 --> 00:04:53,314
But…

72
00:04:55,358 --> 00:04:56,943
if my life had worked out…

73
00:04:59,612 --> 00:05:02,490
would I still be holding onto
and struggling with what happened then?

74
00:05:04,659 --> 00:05:07,537
Am I constantly bringing up my past
as an excuse…

75
00:05:09,580 --> 00:05:11,916
for why my present situation
isn't working out?

76
00:05:15,294 --> 00:05:17,672
How can you not bring up your past?

77
00:05:19,298 --> 00:05:20,967
Aren't you being too hard on yourself?

78
00:05:21,551 --> 00:05:23,594
But you don't do that.

79
00:05:25,930 --> 00:05:27,306
You don't bring up the past

80
00:05:28,599 --> 00:05:30,309
to make excuses about the present.

81
00:05:32,728 --> 00:05:34,480
I don't have a past to bring up.

82
00:05:36,023 --> 00:05:37,316
You may not believe it,

83
00:05:38,109 --> 00:05:38,943
but my family

84
00:05:39,735 --> 00:05:40,653
was pretty well-off.

85
00:05:42,238 --> 00:05:43,990
We were a pretty happy family…

86
00:05:45,950 --> 00:05:47,451
until my sophomore year in college.

87
00:05:48,327 --> 00:05:49,745
When my father's business went under,

88
00:05:49,829 --> 00:05:52,999
all that wealth disappeared overnight.

89
00:05:54,876 --> 00:05:55,710
Then my mother

90
00:05:56,377 --> 00:05:57,211
and father

91
00:05:58,171 --> 00:05:59,422
passed away one after another.

92
00:06:00,590 --> 00:06:04,010
I didn't know everything could collapse
in an instant.

93
00:06:05,261 --> 00:06:08,014
I'm sure many people
found some satisfaction

94
00:06:08,097 --> 00:06:10,266
in seeing our family collapse.

95
00:06:12,143 --> 00:06:12,977
I get it.

96
00:06:13,936 --> 00:06:16,397
It's only fair
if things go back and forth.

97
00:06:17,773 --> 00:06:19,275
What's the point of carrying on

98
00:06:20,067 --> 00:06:21,611
what our parents' generation built?

99
00:06:24,989 --> 00:06:27,408
All of our belongings
from when we were well-off

100
00:06:27,491 --> 00:06:29,619
have been sitting in storage

101
00:06:29,702 --> 00:06:30,703
for the past 20 years.

102
00:06:31,329 --> 00:06:33,748
We pay a hefty rental fee every year.

103
00:06:34,332 --> 00:06:36,125
I see you can't let go of those memories.

104
00:06:38,753 --> 00:06:39,921
They're not so much memories

105
00:06:41,297 --> 00:06:42,757
as proof we used to be well-off.

106
00:06:48,804 --> 00:06:49,931
Without that…

107
00:06:54,602 --> 00:06:56,062
I feel like I have nothing to lean on.

108
00:07:02,818 --> 00:07:03,736
I feel like

109
00:07:04,987 --> 00:07:07,448
I can only let it go
once I've improved even a little.

110
00:07:10,993 --> 00:07:12,078
Once I debut with a bang,

111
00:07:13,579 --> 00:07:15,581
I'm going to throw everything away.

112
00:07:17,416 --> 00:07:18,543
Was that

113
00:07:19,168 --> 00:07:21,045
the hardest time in your life?

114
00:07:29,220 --> 00:07:30,054
No.

115
00:07:37,436 --> 00:07:38,271
I see…

116
00:07:40,523 --> 00:07:42,733
you've never talked about it before.

117
00:07:58,082 --> 00:08:00,835
<i>My favorite sound in the world…</i>

118
00:08:06,048 --> 00:08:08,301
<i>is my brother's snoring.</i>

119
00:08:10,094 --> 00:08:11,679
<i>When I hear him snore…</i>

120
00:08:14,140 --> 00:08:15,308
<i>I feel at ease.</i>

121
00:08:18,436 --> 00:08:19,437
<i>"Oh."</i>

122
00:08:21,105 --> 00:08:22,023
<i>"He's sleeping."</i>

123
00:08:23,190 --> 00:08:24,191
<i>"I can sleep now too."</i>

124
00:08:26,319 --> 00:08:27,987
<i>But if I don't hear anything,</i>

125
00:08:29,655 --> 00:08:31,115
<i>I wonder why he can't sleep.</i>

126
00:08:37,788 --> 00:08:39,874
<i>My life has to improve even a little.</i>

127
00:08:40,916 --> 00:08:42,877
<i>I have to achieve something on my own,</i>
<i>even a little.</i>

128
00:08:43,919 --> 00:08:46,130
<i>That way, I can let go of the past</i>
<i>and my wounds.</i>

129
00:08:47,673 --> 00:08:48,507
<i>That way,</i>

130
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:52,053
<i>I won't feel anxious about you,</i>
<i>Ms. Byeon Eun-a, rising to the heavens,</i>

131
00:08:53,596 --> 00:08:55,973
<i>or worry about why Jin-man can't sleep.</i>

132
00:08:57,391 --> 00:08:58,476
<i>I can't just let go.</i>

133
00:08:59,644 --> 00:09:01,395
<i>Not until I see what I've achieved.</i>

134
00:09:02,438 --> 00:09:03,939
<i>Not until I see what I'm capable of.</i>

135
00:09:15,493 --> 00:09:16,911
Bounce, bounce!

136
00:09:19,455 --> 00:09:20,831
Go, go, go, go, go!

137
00:09:22,833 --> 00:09:23,668
Safe!

138
00:10:05,793 --> 00:10:07,128
Let's go.

139
00:10:15,428 --> 00:10:16,429
Hello.

140
00:10:19,890 --> 00:10:20,891
Thank you.

141
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:30,943
HANKUK UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

142
00:10:35,906 --> 00:10:37,032
Hello.

143
00:10:58,179 --> 00:11:01,140
Goodness, two strong men
to carry things and help me?

144
00:11:01,223 --> 00:11:02,850
I feel so special.

145
00:11:18,532 --> 00:11:20,451
There's no place like home.

146
00:11:41,597 --> 00:11:44,058
I'm usually not the type
to ask for compensation,

147
00:11:45,768 --> 00:11:46,894
but fixing teeth is expensive.

148
00:11:49,897 --> 00:11:52,274
I got a partial denture, not an implant.

149
00:12:03,035 --> 00:12:04,078
I'll get an implant myself

150
00:12:04,161 --> 00:12:05,871
after I make some money.

151
00:12:05,955 --> 00:12:07,414
Send it to my bank account.

152
00:12:20,970 --> 00:12:22,179
DEPOSIT AMOUNT: 1,200,000 WON
SENDER: MA JAE-YEONG

153
00:12:25,849 --> 00:12:28,269
My youngest aunt has two daughters.

154
00:12:28,352 --> 00:12:30,980
Whenever her reckless sons-in-law
give her a headache, she says,

155
00:12:31,605 --> 00:12:36,068
"If my girls had an older brother,
those two wouldn't act like that."

156
00:12:36,151 --> 00:12:37,486
Some assholes think

157
00:12:38,904 --> 00:12:40,364
a women-only household
is easy to deal with.

158
00:12:46,453 --> 00:12:47,371
Just so you know,

159
00:12:48,622 --> 00:12:50,165
it's not just women at Eun-a's house.

160
00:13:08,225 --> 00:13:10,227
I can't go into details,

161
00:13:10,311 --> 00:13:11,186
but…

162
00:13:12,730 --> 00:13:14,565
if you mess with Eun-a,

163
00:13:15,316 --> 00:13:16,150
you'll be

164
00:13:17,234 --> 00:13:18,193
in real trouble.

165
00:13:18,777 --> 00:13:19,695
I'm serious.

166
00:13:20,362 --> 00:13:22,448
Forget about <i>Knock knock knock</i>.

167
00:13:22,531 --> 00:13:23,616
Your film career

168
00:13:24,241 --> 00:13:25,451
could be destroyed.

169
00:13:27,328 --> 00:13:29,496
Just remember that I warned you.

170
00:13:30,122 --> 00:13:34,168
Don't come back later
saying I didn't tell you.

171
00:13:46,680 --> 00:13:47,514
See you.

172
00:13:57,107 --> 00:13:58,233
Episodes five and six synopses ready?

173
00:13:58,317 --> 00:14:00,444
Will you knock before you come in?

174
00:14:02,988 --> 00:14:04,114
Why?

175
00:14:04,198 --> 00:14:05,157
Were you playing games?

176
00:14:05,240 --> 00:14:06,617
I wasn't playing games.

177
00:14:06,700 --> 00:14:08,243
Does it look like I have time to play?

178
00:14:08,952 --> 00:14:10,454
Why isn't Writer Park here?

179
00:14:14,083 --> 00:14:14,958
Why isn't she here?

180
00:14:15,042 --> 00:14:16,752
We decided to write separately.

181
00:14:17,753 --> 00:14:18,754
Why?

182
00:14:20,381 --> 00:14:22,132
You really think
we should work face-to-face?

183
00:14:39,024 --> 00:14:40,985
-Listen carefully.
-Just say it!

184
00:14:41,068 --> 00:14:42,778
My hearing is fine.

185
00:14:44,071 --> 00:14:45,531
What are you, threatening a kid?

186
00:14:46,573 --> 00:14:47,658
"Listen carefully."

187
00:14:53,539 --> 00:14:55,624
I regret yelling at you.

188
00:14:57,167 --> 00:14:58,002
I'm sorry.

189
00:14:58,627 --> 00:15:01,588
You were on a roll for once,
but I ruined it.

190
00:15:06,010 --> 00:15:08,095
I should've just let you be
until you were finished,

191
00:15:09,221 --> 00:15:10,180
but I lost my temper.

192
00:15:11,765 --> 00:15:12,683
I'm sorry.

193
00:15:14,935 --> 00:15:17,187
Just ignore me and keep writing
with that same excitement.

194
00:15:17,271 --> 00:15:18,313
I mean it.

195
00:15:20,691 --> 00:15:21,567
And…

196
00:15:26,530 --> 00:15:28,157
let's get divorced when the time is right.

197
00:15:35,706 --> 00:15:37,374
I've never once brought up divorce

198
00:15:38,125 --> 00:15:40,085
since we got married.

199
00:15:42,337 --> 00:15:44,339
I told myself not to say it out of habit,

200
00:15:45,299 --> 00:15:46,633
but to say it when the time comes.

201
00:15:48,635 --> 00:15:49,887
I think now's the time.

202
00:15:52,014 --> 00:15:53,640
In order to write,

203
00:15:54,224 --> 00:15:56,060
you have to dive into different emotions,

204
00:15:57,603 --> 00:15:59,354
moving from one to the next,

205
00:16:00,397 --> 00:16:02,066
or sometimes be just downright dirty.

206
00:16:03,859 --> 00:16:05,986
You have to use every version of yourself.

207
00:16:07,946 --> 00:16:09,698
But with your wife
looking over your shoulder…

208
00:16:11,700 --> 00:16:13,452
you can't just go for it.

209
00:16:16,789 --> 00:16:19,458
You're boxed into being a man
who won't raise moral questions.

210
00:16:22,878 --> 00:16:25,756
There are couples who freely accept
each other's emotions

211
00:16:25,839 --> 00:16:27,132
and even support them.

212
00:16:28,759 --> 00:16:30,177
But you and I

213
00:16:30,260 --> 00:16:31,720
aren't built like that.

214
00:16:33,722 --> 00:16:37,476
Everyone knows ruthless women write well,
and ruthless men direct well.

215
00:16:37,559 --> 00:16:40,979
If you can't let go
of that half-decent guy in you,

216
00:16:41,772 --> 00:16:43,107
you won't get anywhere.

217
00:16:47,861 --> 00:16:49,238
So getting a divorce

218
00:16:50,447 --> 00:16:52,407
and just going for it
is the right thing to do.

219
00:16:54,993 --> 00:16:56,537
I'm not saying divorce is easy.

220
00:16:57,246 --> 00:16:59,331
I know I'm the one who brought it up,

221
00:16:59,414 --> 00:17:01,500
but I'm not sure if I can actually do it.

222
00:17:02,084 --> 00:17:02,918
But…

223
00:17:05,045 --> 00:17:06,755
I'm just putting it out there

224
00:17:06,839 --> 00:17:08,632
because I want to set you free.

225
00:17:10,759 --> 00:17:12,386
Don't tie yourself down to me.

226
00:17:13,303 --> 00:17:14,805
Just go for it.

227
00:17:15,305 --> 00:17:16,974
It may be hard right now…

228
00:17:20,394 --> 00:17:22,312
but in time, parting will feel natural.

229
00:17:23,939 --> 00:17:24,940
Let's part ways then.

230
00:17:34,783 --> 00:17:36,243
You need to crack into the watermelon.

231
00:17:36,326 --> 00:17:38,078
A sweet, juicy one.

232
00:17:39,204 --> 00:17:40,622
So just go for it, okay?

233
00:17:57,806 --> 00:17:59,766
She really knows how to make a threat.

234
00:18:18,076 --> 00:18:19,536
I went to a dollar store

235
00:18:19,620 --> 00:18:22,122
and asked an employee where something was.

236
00:18:22,206 --> 00:18:24,958
But they said they didn't know
because they haven't been there long.

237
00:18:25,042 --> 00:18:27,753
They said the exact same thing last week,

238
00:18:27,836 --> 00:18:30,380
and then they said it again this week.

239
00:18:30,464 --> 00:18:32,216
If it were me,

240
00:18:32,299 --> 00:18:34,801
I'd have focused
and memorized it all in two days.

241
00:18:34,885 --> 00:18:36,470
I knew they wouldn't be good at their job.

242
00:18:36,553 --> 00:18:37,554
Their face

243
00:18:38,889 --> 00:18:40,182
was slack.

244
00:18:40,933 --> 00:18:42,851
It was as if it couldn't hold any focus.

245
00:18:43,477 --> 00:18:44,519
It was slack.

246
00:18:45,187 --> 00:18:46,813
My friend works at a dollar store too,

247
00:18:46,897 --> 00:18:49,441
and they always want to meet
in front of one.

248
00:18:50,025 --> 00:18:52,402
They'll come ten minutes early

249
00:18:52,486 --> 00:18:56,990
and observe the store's layout
and how the merchandise is displayed.

250
00:18:57,074 --> 00:18:59,409
-They're an assistant branch manager.
-Oh, really?

251
00:18:59,493 --> 00:19:01,536
They became assistant branch manager
in just five years.

252
00:19:02,079 --> 00:19:04,039
They could be working the same job,

253
00:19:04,122 --> 00:19:06,708
but what separates someone who makes it
from someone who doesn't

254
00:19:07,376 --> 00:19:08,710
is focus.

255
00:19:09,753 --> 00:19:12,756
I might be scatterbrained
and all over the place,

256
00:19:12,839 --> 00:19:15,175
but once I focus, I go all in.

257
00:19:16,843 --> 00:19:18,262
Look at my face.

258
00:19:20,180 --> 00:19:22,182
All my focus is right here.

259
00:19:24,101 --> 00:19:26,478
We can start shooting
in the second half of next year.

260
00:19:27,104 --> 00:19:30,107
I already have all the shots and scenes
planned out in my head,

261
00:19:30,732 --> 00:19:32,484
so we can start filming next year,
no problem.

262
00:19:33,068 --> 00:19:34,736
From now on,

263
00:19:35,445 --> 00:19:36,905
get straight to the point.

264
00:19:37,698 --> 00:19:39,533
Tell me the conclusion first.

265
00:19:39,616 --> 00:19:42,202
Then I'll decide whether to listen
to the details.

266
00:19:42,286 --> 00:19:43,996
If you talk like this on set,

267
00:19:44,079 --> 00:19:45,664
it'll take all day.

268
00:19:47,332 --> 00:19:48,583
Got it. Straight to the point.

269
00:19:48,667 --> 00:19:52,254
And I don't care
if you film next year or not.

270
00:19:52,337 --> 00:19:54,256
Based on my schedule,
it's two years from now

271
00:19:54,339 --> 00:19:57,217
because I'm doing a film
with Director Park Jin next year.

272
00:19:57,301 --> 00:20:01,138
But I heard Director Park's screenplay
is still being revised.

273
00:20:01,763 --> 00:20:02,681
You read my screenplay, right?

274
00:20:02,764 --> 00:20:03,807
No, I haven't!

275
00:20:03,890 --> 00:20:05,726
Why would I read something
that won't be filmed for two years?

276
00:20:05,809 --> 00:20:06,685
I haven't even been paid.

277
00:20:08,186 --> 00:20:11,189
There's nothing to revise. It's perfect.

278
00:20:11,273 --> 00:20:12,941
And the investors are already on board.

279
00:20:13,025 --> 00:20:15,319
Be quiet and shut your mouth.

280
00:20:16,069 --> 00:20:16,987
And from now on,

281
00:20:17,070 --> 00:20:19,489
don't come to the set
under any circumstances.

282
00:20:19,573 --> 00:20:20,741
I can't stay in character.

283
00:20:22,659 --> 00:20:23,702
Stand up.

284
00:20:23,785 --> 00:20:25,037
Come here.

285
00:20:25,787 --> 00:20:27,622
Now, lower your head.

286
00:20:30,083 --> 00:20:32,878
Let's just do ten laps today.

287
00:20:32,961 --> 00:20:33,920
Begin.

288
00:20:34,755 --> 00:20:36,214
-One.
-Louder!

289
00:20:36,298 --> 00:20:37,132
One!

290
00:20:37,632 --> 00:20:38,842
-Two!
-Louder!

291
00:20:38,925 --> 00:20:39,843
Three!

292
00:20:39,926 --> 00:20:41,094
Four!

293
00:20:41,178 --> 00:20:43,180
He wants to film two years from now.

294
00:20:43,263 --> 00:20:45,891
I'm going insane.
I'd start tomorrow if I could.

295
00:20:45,974 --> 00:20:47,559
A whole year will go to waste!

296
00:20:47,642 --> 00:20:50,395
You've waited 20 years.
Can't you wait another year?

297
00:20:50,479 --> 00:20:53,440
I've waited 20 years,
so of course I can't wait!

298
00:20:54,232 --> 00:20:56,818
Who knows what kind of mess
Noh Kang-sik will get into again?

299
00:20:57,944 --> 00:21:00,447
I just want to be done with it
before he causes trouble.

300
00:21:00,530 --> 00:21:01,782
<i>Releasing steam.</i>

301
00:21:02,949 --> 00:21:05,077
Okay. I'll call you later.

302
00:21:22,511 --> 00:21:23,762
What's <i>ingan</i> in English?

303
00:21:26,306 --> 00:21:27,641
What is it in English?

304
00:21:27,724 --> 00:21:28,892
Human.

305
00:21:29,476 --> 00:21:30,727
There's another word after that.

306
00:21:32,813 --> 00:21:33,939
Mankind?

307
00:21:34,815 --> 00:21:35,732
Human being.

308
00:21:36,817 --> 00:21:38,485
B-E-I-N-G.

309
00:21:39,444 --> 00:21:41,196
Not "human doing." It's "human being."

310
00:21:43,532 --> 00:21:45,700
So just be still and exist.

311
00:21:47,661 --> 00:21:49,329
Quit rambling about

312
00:21:50,122 --> 00:21:51,665
what you did or didn't do.

313
00:21:51,748 --> 00:21:53,959
Stop running around "doing" things.

314
00:21:54,042 --> 00:21:54,918
Practice "being."

315
00:21:57,170 --> 00:21:58,380
Just be still.

316
00:22:00,382 --> 00:22:02,217
Do you know how hard it is to be still?

317
00:22:03,343 --> 00:22:05,512
Why don't you stop drinking
and just be still?

318
00:22:24,823 --> 00:22:25,782
Did you watch it?

319
00:22:26,658 --> 00:22:27,868
The AI-made movie, that is.

320
00:22:27,951 --> 00:22:29,828
Just a two-line command,

321
00:22:29,911 --> 00:22:34,124
and it pumps out a movie
with an insanely good story and visuals.

322
00:22:34,207 --> 00:22:37,294
What should take years of effort
is done in just a few minutes.

323
00:22:37,377 --> 00:22:40,046
I mean, I knew the AI era was coming,

324
00:22:40,130 --> 00:22:42,174
but I didn't expect it
to catch up this quickly.

325
00:22:43,508 --> 00:22:45,260
Is this the end for us now?

326
00:22:45,343 --> 00:22:47,012
We can't beat machines.

327
00:22:47,095 --> 00:22:51,558
Everyone's racing to catch the last train
before their screenplays go to waste.

328
00:22:52,184 --> 00:22:54,936
I heard they're just throwing them
at investors.

329
00:22:55,520 --> 00:22:57,189
Looks like Gyeong-se
will catch the last train.

330
00:22:57,898 --> 00:22:59,357
They're filming next year.

331
00:22:59,441 --> 00:23:01,860
The streaming company likes the script,
so they're casting right now.

332
00:23:04,237 --> 00:23:06,281
His scripts are always good.

333
00:23:06,364 --> 00:23:09,826
They just never get shot
the way they're written.

334
00:23:09,910 --> 00:23:11,870
Once they start shooting,
it all goes to chaos,

335
00:23:11,953 --> 00:23:14,122
and everything falls apart.

336
00:23:14,206 --> 00:23:17,042
Then the actors get tense and ask,

337
00:23:17,125 --> 00:23:19,085
"Wait, are you sure

338
00:23:19,836 --> 00:23:20,837
this is right?"

339
00:23:20,921 --> 00:23:23,715
That's why he ends up
becoming enemies with the actors.

340
00:23:23,798 --> 00:23:26,009
-I wouldn't say "enemies."
-Hey.

341
00:23:26,885 --> 00:23:29,512
Name one actor he's worked with
that he's still close to.

342
00:23:29,596 --> 00:23:30,764
Jang Mi-ran?

343
00:23:30,847 --> 00:23:32,390
She's still seething

344
00:23:32,474 --> 00:23:33,892
about being fooled by his writing.

345
00:23:33,975 --> 00:23:38,438
The rumor spread among actors,
so casting won't be easy.

346
00:23:38,521 --> 00:23:39,564
It'll be freaking hard.

347
00:23:40,232 --> 00:23:44,027
The only reason he's still a director
is that Hye-jin went around begging

348
00:23:44,110 --> 00:23:46,655
and gave it everything she got.

349
00:23:46,738 --> 00:23:47,989
If it weren't for her,

350
00:23:48,740 --> 00:23:51,534
I'd say he wouldn't have made it.

351
00:23:51,618 --> 00:23:52,911
He would've been executed.

352
00:23:56,957 --> 00:23:57,874
You're here.

353
00:23:57,958 --> 00:23:58,917
Hello.

354
00:24:05,757 --> 00:24:06,800
Cham, cham, cham.

355
00:24:10,470 --> 00:24:11,763
If you ever

356
00:24:12,389 --> 00:24:14,975
go meet an actor without my permission,
you're dead.

357
00:24:15,058 --> 00:24:16,810
Any meetings with actors

358
00:24:16,893 --> 00:24:19,479
or whatever movie-related work
goes through me first. Got it?

359
00:24:23,275 --> 00:24:24,776
Get up already.

360
00:24:24,859 --> 00:24:26,236
Go upstairs and write.

361
00:24:29,990 --> 00:24:32,117
I said go upstairs and write.

362
00:24:35,370 --> 00:24:36,538
Damn it.

363
00:24:42,127 --> 00:24:43,295
What is it?

364
00:24:43,378 --> 00:24:45,297
Did you bad-mouth him
without knowing he was here?

365
00:24:47,674 --> 00:24:49,050
What did you say?

366
00:24:54,472 --> 00:24:55,348
Whatever.

367
00:25:09,821 --> 00:25:11,031
Do you want a drink?

368
00:25:14,909 --> 00:25:16,870
It's all your fault.

369
00:25:16,953 --> 00:25:19,831
-What did I do?
-Why did you say he caught the last train?

370
00:25:19,914 --> 00:25:20,957
But I…

371
00:25:28,006 --> 00:25:29,090
Gyeong-se, have a drink.

372
00:25:32,218 --> 00:25:33,303
Everyone out.

373
00:25:33,386 --> 00:25:34,387
Leave, all of you.

374
00:25:35,472 --> 00:25:36,389
Close up and head home.

375
00:25:36,473 --> 00:25:37,599
They're worse with people around.

376
00:25:38,266 --> 00:25:39,100
Right now?

377
00:25:40,560 --> 00:25:41,978
Start talking after we leave.

378
00:25:45,273 --> 00:25:46,358
I said get up.

379
00:25:46,441 --> 00:25:48,735
Right, we should go. Let's go.

380
00:25:48,818 --> 00:25:51,279
-Hey, where are you going?
-Home, of course.

381
00:26:08,505 --> 00:26:09,422
Sorry, I didn't know.

382
00:26:13,885 --> 00:26:14,886
I wonder

383
00:26:16,471 --> 00:26:18,390
when they'll close your coffin.

384
00:26:20,725 --> 00:26:21,893
This will end.

385
00:26:23,228 --> 00:26:26,398
Our tiresome relationship
will eventually come to an end.

386
00:26:26,481 --> 00:26:29,025
I wonder how it'll end for you,
and how it'll end for me.

387
00:26:31,986 --> 00:26:33,238
"So he dies in the end."

388
00:26:34,489 --> 00:26:37,617
"After all that bullshit
about never dying,

389
00:26:37,700 --> 00:26:39,119
he dies after all."

390
00:26:42,414 --> 00:26:43,748
I want to end it,

391
00:26:45,083 --> 00:26:47,836
but I don't know how,
and it drives me to tears.

392
00:26:49,546 --> 00:26:51,423
Every night, I dream of dragging you

393
00:26:52,507 --> 00:26:54,467
into the age of duels.

394
00:26:56,261 --> 00:26:57,929
<i>If we were in the age of duels…</i>

395
00:26:59,013 --> 00:27:01,641
In the age of duels,
where everything ends in a single blow…

396
00:27:19,492 --> 00:27:21,995
I used to think
while watching foreign films,

397
00:27:23,455 --> 00:27:26,416
"Why would anyone risk their life
over something so trivial?"

398
00:27:27,667 --> 00:27:28,626
But now,

399
00:27:29,419 --> 00:27:30,253
I want to risk it.

400
00:27:31,963 --> 00:27:34,299
I'm so sick of this endless cycle.

401
00:27:34,382 --> 00:27:36,426
I'd rather end it once and for all.

402
00:27:39,137 --> 00:27:41,222
I've thought about why you piss me off.

403
00:27:41,306 --> 00:27:43,099
It's because you have a sixth sense

404
00:27:43,683 --> 00:27:45,268
for where it hurts me the most.

405
00:27:46,311 --> 00:27:48,730
You know exactly what my weak points are,

406
00:27:48,813 --> 00:27:50,523
and you stab right into them

407
00:27:52,192 --> 00:27:53,109
while laughing.

408
00:27:55,695 --> 00:27:57,864
If I were a bigger man,

409
00:27:57,947 --> 00:28:00,700
I'd laugh along with you, but I can't.

410
00:28:02,327 --> 00:28:04,037
And it frustrates the hell out of me.

411
00:28:06,623 --> 00:28:12,003
Everyone stakes their whole life
on being seen as a decent person.

412
00:28:13,129 --> 00:28:16,007
But you always wreck that.

413
00:28:17,550 --> 00:28:21,012
Your sharp tongue keeps stabbing them
like a broken blade.

414
00:28:21,095 --> 00:28:23,765
I was just saying it for fun.

415
00:28:23,848 --> 00:28:26,184
Talking trash about others
is just for laughs.

416
00:28:26,267 --> 00:28:28,561
You'll keep doing it for fun,

417
00:28:29,395 --> 00:28:33,566
and I'll keep bleeding from the blade
you stab me with for fun.

418
00:28:36,903 --> 00:28:38,154
Let's just stop, Dong-man.

419
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:40,114
Okay?

420
00:28:41,449 --> 00:28:42,700
I know you don't like me.

421
00:28:44,702 --> 00:28:45,703
Let's end this.

422
00:28:48,456 --> 00:28:49,624
You want to go on a trip?

423
00:28:50,792 --> 00:28:51,960
How about a four-day trip?

424
00:28:53,044 --> 00:28:53,878
Just the two of us.

425
00:28:57,006 --> 00:28:58,424
Let's spend those four days

426
00:28:59,467 --> 00:29:02,220
letting out all the stuff
we've been holding against each other,

427
00:29:02,303 --> 00:29:04,889
and see who comes out on top
from all this.

428
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:07,600
I won't hold it against you if you do.

429
00:29:09,143 --> 00:29:09,978
Let's end this.

430
00:29:12,647 --> 00:29:13,565
Please.

431
00:29:14,983 --> 00:29:15,859
Okay?

432
00:29:16,818 --> 00:29:17,694
Let's just

433
00:29:18,403 --> 00:29:19,863
end this.

434
00:29:22,699 --> 00:29:23,533
Done.

435
00:29:26,452 --> 00:29:27,287
It's over.

436
00:29:33,626 --> 00:29:34,878
Dong-man.

437
00:29:37,130 --> 00:29:38,172
Dong-man?

438
00:29:40,425 --> 00:29:41,551
Dong-man.

439
00:29:43,887 --> 00:29:44,721
It's over.

440
00:29:46,598 --> 00:29:47,724
Dong-man.

441
00:29:48,975 --> 00:29:50,602
Let's end this.

442
00:29:51,895 --> 00:29:53,104
Dong-man.

443
00:29:54,814 --> 00:29:56,399
Let's end this.

444
00:29:57,400 --> 00:29:58,776
Damn it.

445
00:29:59,569 --> 00:30:02,488
Dong-man, let's just end this!

446
00:30:06,826 --> 00:30:09,287
I just got my tooth fixed!

447
00:30:15,126 --> 00:30:16,669
This isn't new for you.

448
00:30:18,046 --> 00:30:20,632
It's not the first time
you've heard people say

449
00:30:21,633 --> 00:30:23,217
you're a director

450
00:30:23,927 --> 00:30:27,347
who's made five films with no style,
no taste, and no signature work.

451
00:30:27,430 --> 00:30:30,183
You're just pissed
because it's coming from me!

452
00:30:30,266 --> 00:30:31,893
Someone who hasn't even debuted yet!

453
00:30:33,770 --> 00:30:36,522
What, if you're not doing well,
you can't talk trash?

454
00:30:36,606 --> 00:30:39,692
You're just scared that a pathetic loser
like me might catch up to you.

455
00:30:40,276 --> 00:30:42,612
Stop thinking about
crushing the people below you,

456
00:30:42,695 --> 00:30:45,865
and just focus on catching up
with the ones above you!

457
00:30:47,325 --> 00:30:48,451
And let's find out

458
00:30:48,534 --> 00:30:49,786
how you die

459
00:30:50,453 --> 00:30:51,788
and how I die

460
00:30:52,705 --> 00:30:53,831
when the coffin closes.

461
00:30:56,084 --> 00:30:58,044
It's over! The end!

462
00:31:10,848 --> 00:31:12,058
Satisfying! So satisfying!

463
00:31:17,271 --> 00:31:18,773
Damn it.

464
00:31:24,654 --> 00:31:26,239
REGRET

465
00:31:27,448 --> 00:31:28,825
How is this "regret"?

466
00:31:56,728 --> 00:31:57,562
Gyeong-se.

467
00:31:59,397 --> 00:32:00,273
I'm sorry.

468
00:32:01,607 --> 00:32:02,442
I was wrong.

469
00:32:10,283 --> 00:32:11,117
I'm trying

470
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:13,953
not to talk trash about others.

471
00:32:14,954 --> 00:32:15,788
I really

472
00:32:16,789 --> 00:32:18,374
want to stop talking trash about someone

473
00:32:20,334 --> 00:32:22,086
I used to be close to.

474
00:32:24,839 --> 00:32:25,923
But it's not easy.

475
00:32:30,887 --> 00:32:31,888
There's only one way

476
00:32:32,847 --> 00:32:34,557
for us to get back to

477
00:32:35,558 --> 00:32:36,768
being close.

478
00:32:39,062 --> 00:32:40,313
I have to debut.

479
00:32:43,441 --> 00:32:44,734
We need to be on the same level.

480
00:32:46,027 --> 00:32:48,654
That way, you won't dismiss what I say,

481
00:32:49,238 --> 00:32:51,449
and I won't take your words the wrong way.

482
00:32:52,742 --> 00:32:54,702
When we were on the same level,

483
00:32:54,786 --> 00:32:56,704
when we were both nobodies…

484
00:32:59,165 --> 00:33:00,249
we were freaking amazing.

485
00:33:01,417 --> 00:33:03,086
We were full of energy

486
00:33:04,712 --> 00:33:07,507
and stayed up all night
roasting lousy veteran directors.

487
00:33:09,008 --> 00:33:10,259
We were on our knees like this

488
00:33:10,760 --> 00:33:12,845
and watched <i>Billy Elliot.</i>

489
00:33:12,929 --> 00:33:14,263
We watched it repeatedly,

490
00:33:14,889 --> 00:33:16,224
crying every time.

491
00:33:17,350 --> 00:33:18,935
Remember
<i>Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind</i>?

492
00:33:20,978 --> 00:33:23,731
After watching it…

493
00:33:26,025 --> 00:33:27,944
we felt sentimental for days.

494
00:33:31,280 --> 00:33:33,741
Half of the movies I've watched in my life

495
00:33:34,992 --> 00:33:36,661
were with you.

496
00:33:41,624 --> 00:33:44,877
I've been trying so hard
to get close to you again,

497
00:33:46,379 --> 00:33:48,047
trying to be the same as you,

498
00:33:49,006 --> 00:33:51,342
so we could be close again.

499
00:33:53,386 --> 00:33:56,222
But you've been trying hard
to become different from me.

500
00:34:00,393 --> 00:34:01,435
Gyeong-se.

501
00:34:03,062 --> 00:34:04,981
Let's just be the same again.

502
00:34:06,065 --> 00:34:06,899
Please.

503
00:34:07,942 --> 00:34:11,237
I'll debut and come back
so we're on the same level.

504
00:34:13,072 --> 00:34:14,574
Let's just be the same again.

505
00:34:16,200 --> 00:34:17,034
Please?

506
00:34:18,578 --> 00:34:20,037
Let's be the same.

507
00:34:56,157 --> 00:34:57,533
You're here now,

508
00:34:57,617 --> 00:34:59,243
so just apologize and move on.

509
00:34:59,827 --> 00:35:01,162
Think of it as acting.

510
00:35:01,662 --> 00:35:03,497
You're shooting one apology scene

511
00:35:03,581 --> 00:35:04,999
and making 100 million won.

512
00:35:09,337 --> 00:35:10,630
Damn it!

513
00:35:12,798 --> 00:35:13,799
Come on.

514
00:35:23,601 --> 00:35:24,477
There you go.

515
00:35:30,900 --> 00:35:33,319
I'll talk her down
and get her to apologize somehow.

516
00:35:33,819 --> 00:35:34,779
Don't worry.

517
00:35:58,511 --> 00:36:00,304
Ms. Oh, it's time to go.

518
00:36:03,975 --> 00:36:05,601
How many times do I have to say I'm sorry?

519
00:36:05,685 --> 00:36:07,561
You call that being sorry?

520
00:36:07,645 --> 00:36:09,647
Yeah, this is me being sorry!

521
00:36:09,730 --> 00:36:10,940
This is how I act when I'm sorry.

522
00:36:11,023 --> 00:36:13,901
I go on the defensive when I'm sorry.

523
00:36:13,985 --> 00:36:15,903
What, you want me to cry and beg?

524
00:36:15,987 --> 00:36:17,905
I can't do that
because it makes me cringe.

525
00:36:17,989 --> 00:36:20,950
I was wrong, I've committed a grave sin,
and I'm sorry!

526
00:36:21,033 --> 00:36:22,952
Here, I'll let you hit me.

527
00:36:23,536 --> 00:36:24,370
Go ahead.

528
00:36:24,453 --> 00:36:25,997
Just hit me as hard as you want.

529
00:36:26,080 --> 00:36:28,374
Get on your knees and repeat after me!

530
00:36:28,958 --> 00:36:30,918
-"I'm a crazy bitch."
-Yeah, I'm a crazy bitch.

531
00:36:31,002 --> 00:36:33,629
"Jung Hyeon-u never liked me."

532
00:36:34,297 --> 00:36:36,048
For crying out loud.

533
00:36:36,841 --> 00:36:38,217
No? Then go ahead and tank your career.

534
00:36:38,301 --> 00:36:40,303
I'd rather you just hit me.

535
00:36:40,386 --> 00:36:42,263
I'll die at your hands.

536
00:36:42,346 --> 00:36:44,598
Go ahead and hit me! Come on.

537
00:37:12,460 --> 00:37:14,420
It's just as I expected.

538
00:37:15,046 --> 00:37:19,258
Idiots who don't know how to apologize
or how to accept an apology.

539
00:37:21,302 --> 00:37:23,262
Is Jung Hyeon-u into stupid women?

540
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:29,101
I bet you think you can just vent, quit,
and live like any ordinary person.

541
00:37:30,728 --> 00:37:32,355
Having your face out there is a curse.

542
00:37:32,438 --> 00:37:34,190
People will always remember you.

543
00:37:35,191 --> 00:37:36,650
If you open a café,

544
00:37:36,734 --> 00:37:38,694
you'll be the celebrity
who tanked their career

545
00:37:38,778 --> 00:37:40,112
after a hair-pulling fight
with Jang Mi-ran.

546
00:37:40,196 --> 00:37:41,072
If you open a restaurant,

547
00:37:41,655 --> 00:37:43,324
you'll be the celebrity
who tanked their career

548
00:37:43,407 --> 00:37:45,076
after a hair-pulling fight
with Jang Mi-ran.

549
00:37:45,159 --> 00:37:47,161
Even when you become an old grandma,

550
00:37:47,244 --> 00:37:49,121
you'll be the celebrity
who tanked their career

551
00:37:49,205 --> 00:37:51,457
after a hair-pulling fight
with Jang Mi-ran.

552
00:37:52,625 --> 00:37:53,751
It'll follow you forever.

553
00:37:53,834 --> 00:37:55,544
Why would my career get tanked?

554
00:37:55,628 --> 00:37:57,797
The person who grabbed my hair
is the one whose career would tank.

555
00:37:57,880 --> 00:37:58,839
You'll both go down.

556
00:38:00,716 --> 00:38:03,636
If you can't live an ordinary life,

557
00:38:03,719 --> 00:38:06,347
wouldn't it be better to keep appearing

558
00:38:06,430 --> 00:38:09,058
on the big screen or on TV?

559
00:38:09,141 --> 00:38:11,727
I'd be open to doing that,

560
00:38:11,811 --> 00:38:12,812
but your daughter

561
00:38:14,438 --> 00:38:15,898
refuses to apologize properly.

562
00:38:15,981 --> 00:38:16,899
What a joke.

563
00:38:17,608 --> 00:38:18,734
She can't act.

564
00:38:19,318 --> 00:38:22,988
You'll never get the apology scene
that will satisfy you.

565
00:38:25,324 --> 00:38:26,200
Just drop it.

566
00:38:28,119 --> 00:38:31,497
Jang Mi-ran won't be engaging in
any public activities for the next year.

567
00:38:32,081 --> 00:38:34,375
She won't take part in overseas promotion
for the drama.

568
00:38:34,458 --> 00:38:37,378
She'll just pay the penalty and skip it.

569
00:38:37,461 --> 00:38:39,630
The settlement amount
will be delivered separately

570
00:38:39,713 --> 00:38:41,632
to avoid any contact with Jung Hyeon-u.

571
00:38:42,466 --> 00:38:43,843
Is there anything else you want?

572
00:38:44,635 --> 00:38:45,761
Other than her apology, that is.

573
00:38:49,723 --> 00:38:51,851
If there's nothing else, we're done here.

574
00:38:51,934 --> 00:38:53,519
I came in the middle of a shoot.

575
00:38:53,602 --> 00:38:55,938
You'd think she was your real daughter.

576
00:38:57,481 --> 00:38:58,441
Why don't you just cut ties

577
00:38:58,524 --> 00:39:02,194
with your troublesome husband
and stepdaughter

578
00:39:02,278 --> 00:39:05,281
and start taking care of
your long-neglected biological daughter?

579
00:39:05,364 --> 00:39:08,409
That's how most celebrities deal with
troublesome family members.

580
00:39:08,492 --> 00:39:09,869
This is your chance.

581
00:39:09,952 --> 00:39:11,579
I'll release the CCTV footage for you.

582
00:39:11,662 --> 00:39:12,663
Hey.

583
00:39:17,168 --> 00:39:18,461
All right.

584
00:39:18,544 --> 00:39:19,462
Release it.

585
00:39:20,004 --> 00:39:20,838
Do it.

586
00:39:22,339 --> 00:39:24,884
I watched the footage countless times

587
00:39:26,343 --> 00:39:28,471
and wondered how ordinary people
would react to it.

588
00:39:29,305 --> 00:39:32,308
You speak quietly until Mi-ran walks in.

589
00:39:32,391 --> 00:39:35,144
Then you show just how petty you are

590
00:39:35,227 --> 00:39:38,481
by laughing over the top,
tossing your head around.

591
00:39:42,860 --> 00:39:45,529
Don't even think about editing it.
Release the whole thing.

592
00:39:46,697 --> 00:39:47,656
I'm sure you know

593
00:39:47,740 --> 00:39:51,827
Jung Hyeon-u is known for using acting
as an excuse to get into situationships.

594
00:39:51,911 --> 00:39:54,330
When you heard rumors
about him and Jang Mi-ran,

595
00:39:54,413 --> 00:39:57,917
you tried to shut them down
by labeling her a crazy woman

596
00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:59,668
who can't separate acting from reality.

597
00:40:00,377 --> 00:40:02,838
I've met every actress he's done that to.

598
00:40:04,048 --> 00:40:07,051
They said they'll back us
if this gets out.

599
00:40:13,224 --> 00:40:17,728
You have to see it through with idiots
who can't tell when to back off or quit.

600
00:40:18,646 --> 00:40:19,939
Get up. Let's go.

601
00:40:24,902 --> 00:40:27,530
You seem curious, so I'll tell you.

602
00:40:28,405 --> 00:40:29,406
My biological daughter

603
00:40:30,574 --> 00:40:32,326
is far more impressive
than the likes of you.

604
00:40:33,035 --> 00:40:34,078
You don't even compare.

605
00:40:35,329 --> 00:40:37,164
She doesn't cling to anyone for support.

606
00:40:37,790 --> 00:40:40,459
Not men, and not even her parents.

607
00:40:44,588 --> 00:40:45,589
Bye.

608
00:41:05,901 --> 00:41:09,113
Why do I keep getting caught up
in these unpleasant emotions?

609
00:41:10,698 --> 00:41:11,740
Feeling abandoned

610
00:41:12,950 --> 00:41:14,076
and feeling hurt…

611
00:41:17,621 --> 00:41:19,873
I want to stop writing stories like this.

612
00:41:21,542 --> 00:41:24,044
What do you think makes a story feel real?

613
00:41:28,048 --> 00:41:29,049
Emotions.

614
00:41:32,177 --> 00:41:35,931
How did you feel
when you accurately identified an emotion

615
00:41:37,182 --> 00:41:38,434
that appeared on the emotion watch?

616
00:41:45,983 --> 00:41:46,817
A bit…

617
00:41:50,988 --> 00:41:52,781
A bit thinned out.

618
00:41:54,783 --> 00:41:55,618
That's right.

619
00:41:57,036 --> 00:42:00,956
Negative emotions are easier to manage
once they're accurately identified.

620
00:42:02,499 --> 00:42:05,502
At the very least, they won't snowball

621
00:42:05,586 --> 00:42:07,171
into more distorted thinking.

622
00:42:08,380 --> 00:42:10,049
As your emotions thin out,

623
00:42:10,132 --> 00:42:13,010
the story naturally loses its strength.

624
00:42:14,470 --> 00:42:15,554
<i>Eun-a,</i>

625
00:42:16,180 --> 00:42:18,307
<i>you've practiced</i>
<i>identifying emotions enough</i>

626
00:42:18,974 --> 00:42:21,477
<i>that you can probably do it</i>
<i>without the emotion watch now.</i>

627
00:42:23,145 --> 00:42:24,146
<i>You should give it a try.</i>

628
00:42:25,147 --> 00:42:27,191
<i>Practice accurately identifying emotions.</i>

629
00:42:35,282 --> 00:42:36,700
-Hello.
-Hello.

630
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:40,204
-Hello.
-Goodness. Welcome, Ms. Oh.

631
00:42:40,871 --> 00:42:41,705
This way, please.

632
00:42:44,833 --> 00:42:45,668
Go in.

633
00:42:51,006 --> 00:42:51,840
Hello.

634
00:42:59,098 --> 00:43:01,475
This is Producer Byeon Eun-a.
She's one of our development producers.

635
00:43:01,558 --> 00:43:04,812
She has pretty great ideas.

636
00:43:04,895 --> 00:43:07,523
I'm sure she'll be helpful
in this revision meeting.

637
00:43:08,774 --> 00:43:09,608
Take a seat.

638
00:43:14,071 --> 00:43:16,448
Is the writer still against me
playing the role?

639
00:43:21,120 --> 00:43:22,788
No, it's not that they're against it.

640
00:43:23,414 --> 00:43:27,376
They just want to
think it over more carefully.

641
00:43:27,459 --> 00:43:29,086
They seem a bit full of themselves

642
00:43:29,169 --> 00:43:32,715
because it's a good screenplay
and all the actors are after it.

643
00:43:33,298 --> 00:43:34,591
Please tell the writer

644
00:43:34,675 --> 00:43:36,301
that they're not in a position
to turn me down.

645
00:43:37,886 --> 00:43:41,056
It's well written for a beginner,
but it's not first-rate yet.

646
00:43:42,349 --> 00:43:43,559
I'm sorry.

647
00:43:43,642 --> 00:43:47,354
I'm not sure how much of the writing
comes from the director versus the writer.

648
00:43:48,272 --> 00:43:49,815
But you should hear this, Director Ma.

649
00:43:52,609 --> 00:43:53,777
KNOCK KNOCK KNOCK
BY MA JAE-YEONG, BYEON EUN-A

650
00:43:54,361 --> 00:43:58,323
Go home and count how many times
"like crazy" appears.

651
00:43:59,158 --> 00:44:01,994
"Run like crazy," "Eat like crazy,"

652
00:44:02,077 --> 00:44:03,704
"Swear like crazy."

653
00:44:04,747 --> 00:44:06,248
"Like crazy" means

654
00:44:07,416 --> 00:44:11,628
the actor is expected to overact
and make up for an empty scene.

655
00:44:13,922 --> 00:44:17,301
Scenes that should be
carefully thought through and developed

656
00:44:17,926 --> 00:44:20,429
are reduced to one very lazy direction.

657
00:44:22,514 --> 00:44:26,059
Why should an actor work like crazy
over such lazy writing?

658
00:44:27,227 --> 00:44:28,645
There are quite a few parts like this

659
00:44:28,729 --> 00:44:32,024
that pretend there's substance
and gloss over it.

660
00:44:33,025 --> 00:44:35,360
If you strip them away,

661
00:44:35,444 --> 00:44:36,361
you'll see

662
00:44:37,446 --> 00:44:38,906
the emptiness underneath.

663
00:44:40,449 --> 00:44:43,410
This isn't the time to argue about

664
00:44:43,494 --> 00:44:45,829
whether the protagonist should be female.

665
00:44:48,081 --> 00:44:51,168
When unpleasant emotions surface…

666
00:44:53,462 --> 00:44:55,506
try to pin them down precisely right then

667
00:44:56,381 --> 00:44:57,466
so they don't get out of hand.

668
00:45:00,469 --> 00:45:02,054
<i>The feeling of having been attacked.</i>

669
00:45:02,137 --> 00:45:05,807
Even if it's an idiom, don't use it
if you're not familiar with it.

670
00:45:05,891 --> 00:45:07,017
<i>Fear.</i>

671
00:45:07,100 --> 00:45:08,143
And then

672
00:45:08,727 --> 00:45:10,521
examine the root.

673
00:45:12,856 --> 00:45:14,942
<i>What is the root of this emotion?</i>

674
00:45:15,609 --> 00:45:17,903
This is what beginners do.

675
00:45:29,164 --> 00:45:30,082
<i>However…</i>

676
00:45:31,792 --> 00:45:33,252
<i>I will not die.</i>

677
00:45:35,796 --> 00:45:36,630
<i>I'm not someone…</i>

678
00:45:39,424 --> 00:45:41,677
<i>who can be killed by your words.</i>

679
00:46:26,179 --> 00:46:27,222
It's okay.

680
00:46:28,307 --> 00:46:29,391
I understand.

681
00:46:30,851 --> 00:46:32,561
You don't have to explain.

682
00:46:37,024 --> 00:46:38,233
I hope you know

683
00:46:38,859 --> 00:46:40,944
that I really enjoyed working with you.

684
00:46:44,740 --> 00:46:46,033
Whenever I tried to write,

685
00:46:46,116 --> 00:46:50,120
it felt like 100 people
were waiting in line to criticize me.

686
00:46:51,830 --> 00:46:55,334
But seeing you get excited
over my writing and ideas,

687
00:46:56,043 --> 00:46:59,588
I thought,
"Hey, I guess I'm not bad at writing."

688
00:47:03,550 --> 00:47:05,218
I'm enjoying writing again,

689
00:47:05,844 --> 00:47:07,012
like a teenage girl.

690
00:47:12,684 --> 00:47:15,479
All right, I'm off to choir practice.

691
00:47:16,355 --> 00:47:18,023
I've been trying too hard for a while,

692
00:47:18,106 --> 00:47:20,817
so I'm just going to pretend to sing
and ride on their coattails.

693
00:47:25,614 --> 00:47:27,866
Being a writer is really brutal.

694
00:47:27,949 --> 00:47:31,286
You're on your own from the start,
so you can't ride on anyone's coattails.

695
00:47:33,914 --> 00:47:35,248
In our next life,

696
00:47:35,874 --> 00:47:38,001
