00:57:33,137 --> 00:57:37,308
I had no idea I'd see that leather coat
even in the middle of summer.

786
00:57:46,985 --> 00:57:48,236
WEATHER MAKER
WRITTEN &amp; DIRECTED BY HWANG DONG-MAN

787
00:57:54,242 --> 00:57:55,952
KICKOFF CEREMONY FOR A SAFE SHOOT
AND GREAT SUCCESS FOR WEATHER MAKER

788
00:58:01,791 --> 00:58:02,834
Hello, everyone.

789
00:58:04,377 --> 00:58:06,671
I'm Director Hwang Dong-man.

790
00:58:10,258 --> 00:58:11,259
Hwang Dong-man!

791
00:58:11,342 --> 00:58:12,719
Hwang Dong-man!

792
00:58:15,179 --> 00:58:17,056
I'm honored to be working with you.

793
00:58:17,140 --> 00:58:19,267
I just have a few words to say.

794
00:58:19,350 --> 00:58:20,184
First off,

795
00:58:21,019 --> 00:58:23,146
-let me tell you a story about this coat.
-Goodness gracious.

796
00:58:23,229 --> 00:58:25,690
-This took part in World War II…
-Come on!

797
00:58:25,773 --> 00:58:27,317
Is there anyone here who doesn't know?

798
00:58:27,400 --> 00:58:29,277
Please just listen.

799
00:58:29,360 --> 00:58:31,404
-There's a twist.
-That damn bastard.

800
00:58:31,487 --> 00:58:32,780
Do whatever you want.

801
00:58:32,864 --> 00:58:35,533
I bought this at a flea market
when I went to the Berlin Film Festival

802
00:58:35,617 --> 00:58:37,827
and was told that it was worn
by a Russian soldier during World War II.

803
00:58:37,910 --> 00:58:41,623
I thought if I wore the clothes of someone
who stood in the center of history,

804
00:58:41,706 --> 00:58:44,083
maybe I could step into history myself.

805
00:58:44,167 --> 00:58:45,501
I paid a fortune for it

806
00:58:45,585 --> 00:58:49,380
and made a point of wearing it
for every important occasion.

807
00:58:49,464 --> 00:58:52,800
Then I got into a life-or-death fight
with someone I absolutely hated,

808
00:58:52,884 --> 00:58:54,218
and it got torn.

809
00:58:54,844 --> 00:58:55,678
Oh boy.

810
00:58:57,263 --> 00:58:58,097
That's when I saw

811
00:58:59,057 --> 00:59:02,477
a date clearly stamped into the leather.

812
00:59:03,061 --> 00:59:04,687
It said 1998.

813
00:59:06,856 --> 00:59:08,399
That's right. I was scammed.

814
00:59:08,483 --> 00:59:09,525
Of course.

815
00:59:10,193 --> 00:59:12,278
So did I lose my affection for this coat?

816
00:59:12,362 --> 00:59:13,529
Nope.

817
00:59:13,613 --> 00:59:17,033
This coat
came with a story full of twists,

818
00:59:17,116 --> 00:59:20,536
so I ended up loving it
even more and more and more and more.

819
00:59:21,454 --> 00:59:22,955
This is what we do. Storytelling.

820
00:59:24,248 --> 00:59:25,792
We love,

821
00:59:25,875 --> 00:59:26,834
we get hurt,

822
00:59:27,877 --> 00:59:29,045
and we regret.

823
00:59:30,213 --> 00:59:32,799
We might as well be dead without stories.

824
00:59:32,882 --> 00:59:34,425
We got it, Director Hwang.

825
00:59:34,509 --> 00:59:35,927
Keep it short!

826
00:59:36,928 --> 00:59:37,762
Okay.

827
00:59:39,138 --> 00:59:40,098
My brother

828
00:59:40,890 --> 00:59:42,600
doesn't watch movies.

829
00:59:43,351 --> 00:59:46,938
Even when his younger brother
pitches an absolute fit to make a movie,

830
00:59:47,689 --> 00:59:48,690
he doesn't care.

831
00:59:49,273 --> 00:59:50,400
He doesn't watch them.

832
00:59:51,901 --> 00:59:52,735
<i>He said</i>

833
00:59:53,277 --> 00:59:54,904
<i>he doesn't like stories.</i>

834
00:59:57,323 --> 00:59:58,491
All stories

835
01:00:00,076 --> 01:00:02,036
are just cries that we exist.

836
01:00:03,913 --> 01:00:05,748
<i>"I exist in such a painful way."</i>

837
01:00:08,000 --> 01:00:09,836
<i>"I exist in such a sad way."</i>

838
01:00:12,046 --> 01:00:13,673
<i>"I exist in such a depressed way."</i>

839
01:00:16,884 --> 01:00:18,553
<i>"I exist in such a humorous way."</i>

840
01:00:27,729 --> 01:00:28,896
<i>We get 100 years at best.</i>

841
01:00:30,815 --> 01:00:33,192
<i>Everything disappears in 100 years…</i>

842
01:00:35,445 --> 01:00:37,822
<i>so does anything truly exist</i>
<i>if it disappears?</i>

843
01:00:40,158 --> 01:00:42,076
<i>To lay those doubts to rest…</i>

844
01:00:44,328 --> 01:00:46,581
<i>you end up desperately writing stories.</i>

845
01:00:54,297 --> 01:00:55,548
-We're in sync.
-In sync.

846
01:00:59,177 --> 01:01:00,344
If you have to write stories…

847
01:01:03,264 --> 01:01:04,766
for as long as you live…

848
01:01:07,018 --> 01:01:08,644
you might as well make them humorous.

849
01:01:10,605 --> 01:01:12,356
I couldn't live that way…

850
01:01:14,859 --> 01:01:15,818
but you can live with humor.

851
01:01:20,323 --> 01:01:22,533
We'll run into many obstacles
while filming,

852
01:01:23,826 --> 01:01:26,245
but I'll barrel through them
like a maniac!

853
01:01:26,329 --> 01:01:27,288
Thank you!

854
01:01:29,248 --> 01:01:30,291
Make it big!

855
01:01:36,923 --> 01:01:37,757
Quiet on set!

856
01:01:38,966 --> 01:01:42,386
<i>I don't know how far this film will reach,</i>

857
01:01:42,470 --> 01:01:44,055
<i>but I'm praying with all my heart.</i>

858
01:01:45,306 --> 01:01:47,391
<i>I hope it never wounds anyone.</i>

859
01:01:48,351 --> 01:01:49,977
<i>I hope it can make a sad person smile…</i>

860
01:01:50,061 --> 01:01:50,978
Ready.

861
01:01:51,062 --> 01:01:53,272
<i>-…if only for a moment.</i>
-Scene 23, shot 1, take 1.

862
01:01:53,356 --> 01:01:56,025
<i>I hope it becomes a moment</i>
<i>that opens someone's heart.</i>

863
01:01:56,108 --> 01:01:56,943
Action.

864
01:02:10,957 --> 01:02:12,208
Two, three, up!

865
01:03:10,391 --> 01:03:12,393
NAM GYU-CHEOL

866
01:03:12,476 --> 01:03:14,020
<i>The person you are trying to reach</i>
<i>is on another call.</i>

867
01:03:14,103 --> 01:03:16,522
<i>You will be redirected to voicemail.</i>

868
01:03:16,606 --> 01:03:19,066
<i>Charges will apply once you are connected.</i>

869
01:03:19,150 --> 01:03:21,819
NAM GYU-CHEOL

870
01:03:51,307 --> 01:03:52,600
I'm sorry, Jin-man.

871
01:03:53,309 --> 01:03:55,519
I won't ask for this kind of favor again.

872
01:03:56,062 --> 01:03:59,315
It's just that there isn't a poet like you
that I know of.

873
01:04:00,316 --> 01:04:01,901
It was announced as two hours,

874
01:04:01,984 --> 01:04:03,819
but you can just do one.

875
01:04:07,323 --> 01:04:09,408
Poet Hwang Jin-man,
I heard critics were very excited

876
01:04:09,492 --> 01:04:11,869
when you made your literary debut.

877
01:04:12,703 --> 01:04:13,537
But…

878
01:04:14,288 --> 01:04:16,791
it's been ten years
since your last poetry book came out.

879
01:04:17,416 --> 01:04:19,543
I'm curious why you stopped writing.

880
01:04:20,127 --> 01:04:22,546
I heard you've been drifting
between manual labor jobs.

881
01:04:23,631 --> 01:04:25,591
Is it that
you don't have much to write about?

882
01:04:26,217 --> 01:04:30,137
Or that a welder who writes poetry
is more striking than just a poet?

883
01:04:30,763 --> 01:04:34,183
Are you trying to give your identity
a stronger presence?

884
01:04:34,976 --> 01:04:36,185
I'd like to know.

885
01:04:36,268 --> 01:04:37,728
What does "drifting" mean?

886
01:04:43,484 --> 01:04:45,194
"Drifting."

887
01:04:46,529 --> 01:04:49,031
"To move from place to place
without deciding on a destination."

888
01:04:54,829 --> 01:04:55,913
I've decided.

889
01:04:56,914 --> 01:04:57,748
It's welding.

890
01:04:58,916 --> 01:05:00,292
When there's no work,

891
01:05:01,252 --> 01:05:03,212
I harvest napa cabbage and radishes.

892
01:05:03,796 --> 01:05:07,508
It's fine to move from place to place
without deciding on a destination.

893
01:05:14,056 --> 01:05:16,475
I shouldn't get hung up
on words like this,

894
01:05:17,143 --> 01:05:19,353
but the fact that I still do

895
01:05:20,021 --> 01:05:21,564
means I have a ways to go.

896
01:05:22,606 --> 01:05:23,691
This is what I don't like.

897
01:05:24,817 --> 01:05:26,193
I don't like the distorted view

898
01:05:26,819 --> 01:05:30,906
that poets who become welders
do it to build some special identity.

899
01:05:32,158 --> 01:05:34,368
If that's such a great identity,

900
01:05:34,994 --> 01:05:36,328
then let's all just quit

901
01:05:37,580 --> 01:05:39,165
and become welders.

902
01:05:45,921 --> 01:05:47,006
To be honest…

903
01:05:50,885 --> 01:05:52,803
I like welding more than poetry.

904
01:05:53,512 --> 01:05:54,513
I guess I should say

905
01:05:55,139 --> 01:05:56,348
it suits me better.

906
01:05:58,976 --> 01:06:01,979
Writing poetry was a continuous cycle
of frustration and self-loathing.

907
01:06:02,063 --> 01:06:03,105
But with welding…

908
01:06:05,858 --> 01:06:08,152
I just keep running the torch,
and it gets the work done.

909
01:06:10,488 --> 01:06:12,364
My mind isn't restless.

910
01:06:15,242 --> 01:06:17,661
When I put the welding rod down
and walk away,

911
01:06:17,745 --> 01:06:19,080
all sorts of thoughts

912
01:06:19,163 --> 01:06:21,624
come rushing back again.

913
01:06:23,626 --> 01:06:26,420
But while I'm welding, they don't surface.

914
01:06:29,799 --> 01:06:31,801
It feels like I'm resting
for the first time.

915
01:06:32,510 --> 01:06:33,552
I'm working,

916
01:06:34,887 --> 01:06:36,138
but it feels like resting.

917
01:06:43,687 --> 01:06:44,522
So yes.

918
01:06:46,816 --> 01:06:47,733
I like welding

919
01:06:49,151 --> 01:06:50,569
more than poetry.

920
01:07:00,412 --> 01:07:01,747
Hello.

921
01:07:03,707 --> 01:07:04,583
Hello.

922
01:07:05,709 --> 01:07:06,877
It's been a long time.

923
01:07:23,644 --> 01:07:24,728
Excuse me.

924
01:07:30,234 --> 01:07:31,152
What is it now?

925
01:07:32,862 --> 01:07:34,905
Did Dong-man ask you to check
whether I'm drinking?

926
01:07:35,865 --> 01:07:36,824
No.

927
01:07:36,907 --> 01:07:38,242
It's not that.

928
01:07:42,413 --> 01:07:45,374
I have some fans overseas.

929
01:07:45,457 --> 01:07:46,375
So?

930
01:07:47,001 --> 01:07:50,754
I heard some things,
so I posted something on social media

931
01:07:52,298 --> 01:07:53,382
to look for Yeong-sil.

932
01:07:55,759 --> 01:07:57,178
I'm sorry I did that without asking first.

933
01:07:58,679 --> 01:08:01,140
But I received a DM
from someone in Finland.

934
01:08:12,193 --> 01:08:15,696
They say their child was born in 2012,
and her name is Hwang Yeong-sil.

935
01:08:19,074 --> 01:08:21,410
I deleted part of her first name,

936
01:08:21,493 --> 01:08:23,537
and only mentioned her
as "Hwang Blank-sil,"

937
01:08:23,621 --> 01:08:26,040
but they replied with the exact full name,
"Hwang Yeong-sil."

938
01:09:30,813 --> 01:09:32,856
<i>Spring always waits</i>

939
01:09:33,857 --> 01:09:35,317
<i>It waits for the first snow</i>

940
01:09:36,360 --> 01:09:38,237
<i>It waits for the autumn sky</i>

941
01:09:39,530 --> 01:09:41,615
<i>It waits for every season</i>

942
01:09:44,368 --> 01:09:45,286
<i>But it's right now</i>

943
01:09:46,495 --> 01:09:50,291
<i>Spring, summer, fall, winter</i>

944
01:09:51,583 --> 01:09:53,127
<i>It's all right now</i>

945
01:09:55,004 --> 01:09:56,463
<i>Leaves move in the wind</i>

946
01:09:57,172 --> 01:09:58,048
<i>Flashing white</i>

947
01:09:59,425 --> 01:10:00,426
<i>As they turn</i>

948
01:10:15,941 --> 01:10:18,319
DIRECTOR HWANG DONG-MAN

949
01:10:20,195 --> 01:10:21,405
<i>Don't freak out, okay?</i>

950
01:10:24,199 --> 01:10:25,117
<i>Apparently,</i>

951
01:10:26,493 --> 01:10:27,745
<i>Dong-man has gone quiet.</i>

952
01:10:29,371 --> 01:10:30,706
I think he's having a mental breakdown.

953
01:10:34,835 --> 01:10:37,004
<i>None of the scenes are going as planned,</i>

954
01:10:37,629 --> 01:10:40,215
<i>and the crew</i>
<i>is starting to lose faith in him,</i>

955
01:10:41,258 --> 01:10:44,970
<i>so Noh Kang-sik has been giving cues</i>
<i>and running the set for the past few days.</i>

956
01:10:46,680 --> 01:10:48,849
<i>Directors go through this sometimes.</i>

957
01:10:48,932 --> 01:10:50,100
<i>It's not unusual, but…</i>

958
01:10:51,560 --> 01:10:53,354
<i>I was just wondering how to handle this.</i>

959
01:11:17,836 --> 01:11:18,670
Hey, you.

960
01:11:20,381 --> 01:11:21,298
Get up.

961
01:11:26,345 --> 01:11:27,304
Listen.

962
01:11:28,013 --> 01:11:30,808
Do you want to die by my hand today,
or do you want to film?

963
01:11:31,392 --> 01:11:33,018
Choose one or the other.

964
01:11:33,602 --> 01:11:34,728
Do you want to film?

965
01:11:34,812 --> 01:11:35,854
Or do you want to die?

966
01:11:36,814 --> 01:11:37,731
Do you want to film?

967
01:11:39,024 --> 01:11:40,317
Or do you want to die, you bastard?

968
01:11:41,193 --> 01:11:43,862
<i>If you have to write stories</i>
<i>for as long as you live…</i>

969
01:11:43,946 --> 01:11:45,531
<i>Start filming already, you bastard!</i>

970
01:11:45,614 --> 01:11:46,824
<i>Start filming!</i>

971
01:11:54,248 --> 01:11:55,290
<i>If you have to write stories…</i>

972
01:11:59,253 --> 01:12:00,879
<i>for as long as you live…</i>

973
01:12:28,949 --> 01:12:30,659
Crazy bastard.

974
01:12:35,497 --> 01:12:36,331
Ready.

975
01:12:38,000 --> 01:12:38,917
Action!

976
01:13:08,530 --> 01:13:09,531
<i>Do you know</i>

977
01:13:10,240 --> 01:13:11,825
<i>what weather is?</i>

978
01:13:12,576 --> 01:13:14,161
<i>Do you know how terrifying…</i>

979
01:13:16,079 --> 01:13:17,831
<i>uncontrollable nature can be?</i>

980
01:13:23,170 --> 01:13:25,088
<i>I like how uncontrollable things</i>

981
01:13:26,632 --> 01:13:28,050
<i>exist</i>

982
01:13:29,218 --> 01:13:30,052
<i>in the world.</i>

983
01:13:32,095 --> 01:13:33,680
<i>It makes me feel like…</i>

984
01:13:36,767 --> 01:13:38,393
<i>I might be</i>

985
01:13:39,770 --> 01:13:41,230
<i>something uncontrollable</i>

986
01:13:42,481 --> 01:13:43,315
<i>as well.</i>

987
01:14:26,400 --> 01:14:27,442
<i>It makes me feel like</i>

988
01:14:28,527 --> 01:14:29,861
<i>I might be something…</i>

989
01:14:31,697 --> 01:14:33,407
<i>uncontrollable as well.</i>

990
01:15:30,088 --> 01:15:31,923
-Please enjoy!
-Thank you.

991
01:15:32,007 --> 01:15:34,635
-I had to sit, but--
-Let's hit ten million!

992
01:15:40,223 --> 01:15:41,683
What did they say about the movie?

993
01:15:42,309 --> 01:15:43,310
-Well, they…
-Oh man.

994
01:15:45,020 --> 01:15:49,232
I finally adjusted to digital from film.

995
01:15:49,316 --> 01:15:50,859
But what the hell?

996
01:15:50,942 --> 01:15:51,860
Now it's AI.

997
01:15:53,654 --> 01:15:58,075
So I thought long and hard
about whether to give up,

998
01:15:58,158 --> 01:15:58,992
but today,

999
01:15:59,868 --> 01:16:01,495
I saw Dong-man's film and made a decision.

1000
01:16:02,120 --> 01:16:04,122
AI era or not,

1001
01:16:05,165 --> 01:16:06,500
I'm going to keep writing.

1002
01:16:06,583 --> 01:16:07,959
I'll keep writing to the end,

1003
01:16:09,211 --> 01:16:10,921
and keep filming to the end!

1004
01:16:13,090 --> 01:16:14,091
Let's do it!

1005
01:16:20,263 --> 01:16:22,265
That was great. Well said.

1006
01:16:23,016 --> 01:16:24,351
Hwang Dong-man.

1007
01:16:25,686 --> 01:16:27,104
I knew you'd turn out--

1008
01:16:27,187 --> 01:16:28,772
Don't say you knew I'd turn out well!

1009
01:16:29,481 --> 01:16:30,732
You guys know, right?

1010
01:16:30,816 --> 01:16:32,567
I never miss out on a sure bet.

1011
01:16:32,651 --> 01:16:34,111
Let's sign a contract!

1012
01:16:34,194 --> 01:16:35,278
I'll pay you top rate.

1013
01:16:36,905 --> 01:16:38,907
You're annoying to the very end.

1014
01:16:41,201 --> 01:16:42,160
I love you.

1015
01:16:42,244 --> 01:16:43,954
I love you!

1016
01:16:45,247 --> 01:16:46,623
What an amazing guy.

1017
01:16:46,707 --> 01:16:47,666
He pulled it off!

1018
01:16:48,542 --> 01:16:49,710
What the heck?

1019
01:16:49,793 --> 01:16:50,836
What is it?

1020
01:16:50,919 --> 01:16:54,548
Do you want to have conversations
with me now?

1021
01:16:54,631 --> 01:16:55,841
You know what?

1022
01:16:57,259 --> 01:16:58,301
I love this bastard.

1023
01:16:58,927 --> 01:17:01,138
I think I can even kiss him.

1024
01:17:02,639 --> 01:17:03,807
Stop it!

1025
01:17:03,890 --> 01:17:04,766
What's wrong with you?

1026
01:17:11,606 --> 01:17:12,774
Hey, Gyeong-se.

1027
01:17:14,860 --> 01:17:16,528
So? Do you like the movie?

1028
01:17:18,905 --> 01:17:20,449
-I love it.
-Yeah?

1029
01:17:21,283 --> 01:17:24,619
You know, Dong-man told me
the protagonist is you.

1030
01:17:24,703 --> 01:17:25,537
What?

1031
01:17:26,538 --> 01:17:29,875
"A sentimental punk
who can't be ruthless when it counts

1032
01:17:29,958 --> 01:17:31,376
and ends up perishing."

1033
01:17:32,169 --> 01:17:33,128
He said that's you.

1034
01:17:34,045 --> 01:17:35,756
I've acted a lot in my life,

1035
01:17:36,423 --> 01:17:38,633
but I never thought I'd act out your life.

1036
01:17:38,717 --> 01:17:42,262
Sir, I've written 14 screenplays
over the past 20 years.

1037
01:17:42,888 --> 01:17:45,307
Twelve of them are about Park Gyeong-se.

1038
01:17:46,141 --> 01:17:48,477
He's the most pathetic,

1039
01:17:48,560 --> 01:17:50,270
and the most…

1040
01:17:53,565 --> 01:17:55,192
lovable guy in the world.

1041
01:17:58,111 --> 01:17:59,196
Just you wait.

1042
01:17:59,279 --> 01:18:02,866
There are 11 more Park Gyeong-se stories
yet to come out.

1043
01:18:07,662 --> 01:18:09,331
Do you know <i>The Lustful Bottle Opener</i>
is about you?

1044
01:18:09,915 --> 01:18:11,875
Hey, I'm not that pathetic!

1045
01:18:11,958 --> 01:18:13,168
It's about you.

1046
01:18:13,251 --> 01:18:14,795
No, it's not!

1047
01:18:16,630 --> 01:18:20,383
Now that we're on the same level,
are you ready for some roasting?

1048
01:18:20,467 --> 01:18:21,968
-I sure am.
-Are you ready?

1049
01:18:22,052 --> 01:18:23,094
I sure am. Are you ready?

1050
01:18:23,178 --> 01:18:25,639
All right, then. Ready, action!

1051
01:18:25,722 --> 01:18:28,099
There's this scene
where Mr. Noh meets Yeong-hun.

1052
01:18:28,183 --> 01:18:31,937
As he ran, I wanted to follow him
with a Steadicam like this,

1053
01:18:32,020 --> 01:18:36,107
but the DP insisted on
using a camera dolly

1054
01:18:36,191 --> 01:18:37,317
and following horizontally.

1055
01:18:37,400 --> 01:18:38,860
And you know
Mr. Noh does whatever he wants.

1056
01:18:38,944 --> 01:18:42,781
So he just goes to the front, and the DP
had laid out the camera dolly until…

1057
01:18:42,864 --> 01:18:46,660
<i>I wish I could spend my whole life</i>
<i>just watching you.</i>

1058
01:18:46,743 --> 01:18:48,578
Hey, that's nothing!

1059
01:18:48,662 --> 01:18:50,121
-Remember that car explosion scene?
-Yeah.

1060
01:18:50,205 --> 01:18:52,457
<i>Even if you don't create anything great…</i>

1061
01:18:52,541 --> 01:18:54,334
Cut. Okay!

1062
01:18:54,417 --> 01:18:56,711
<i>It's always comedy with you, like now.</i>

1063
01:18:59,005 --> 01:19:01,842
<i>Even when you step into a burning pit,</i>
<i>it's still comedy.</i>

1064
01:19:01,925 --> 01:19:04,177
And the makeup team.

1065
01:19:04,261 --> 01:19:05,595
-Wait, wasn't it Jun?
-Yeah, Jun!

1066
01:19:05,679 --> 01:19:07,180
<i>Depressing stories,</i>

1067
01:19:07,264 --> 01:19:08,223
<i>sad stories,</i>

1068
01:19:09,140 --> 01:19:10,058
<i>tragic stories…</i>

1069
01:19:12,269 --> 01:19:15,856
<i>I want to keep watching you</i>
<i>turn everything into a comedy.</i>

1070
01:19:25,615 --> 01:19:27,826
<i>The 48th Korean Film Awards</i>

1071
01:19:27,909 --> 01:19:29,327
<i>Best New Director Award goes to…</i>

1072
01:19:31,288 --> 01:19:34,457
<i>Hwang Dong-man for </i>Weather Maker<i>!</i>

1073
01:19:39,170 --> 01:19:45,802
48TH KOREAN FILM AWARDS
BEST NEW DIRECTOR AWARD

1074
01:19:49,431 --> 01:19:51,892
Congratulations, Hwang Dong-man!

1075
01:20:09,034 --> 01:20:09,868
Jin-man!

1076
01:20:11,536 --> 01:20:12,871
I won an award!

1077
01:20:14,456 --> 01:20:16,875
You can look me up online now!

1078
01:20:18,376 --> 01:20:19,502
Yeong-sil!

1079
01:20:20,420 --> 01:20:22,297
You can look up your uncle online now!

1080
01:20:23,965 --> 01:20:25,091
Eun-a!

1081
01:20:30,513 --> 01:20:31,556
Thank you so much

1082
01:20:33,183 --> 01:20:34,726
for being with me.

1083
01:20:36,353 --> 01:20:37,479
<i>From here on,</i>

1084
01:20:38,563 --> 01:20:40,482
<i>I'll work even harder!</i>

1085
01:20:41,399 --> 01:20:42,609
<i>Thank you!</i>

1086
01:20:46,279 --> 01:20:48,073
WE ARE ALL TRYING HERE

1087
01:21:42,502 --> 01:21:43,336
<i>Ready.</i>

1088
01:21:44,212 --> 01:21:45,046
<i>Action.</i>

1089
01:21:55,932 --> 01:22:00,937
Subtitle translation by: Jenny Kim

